  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add the <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> and top with a large knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the corn until tightly sealed and add to a baking tray, then put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the corn is tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623662670337-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623662670337-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623662670337-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623662670337-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623662670337-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the corn is in the oven, rinse the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> until the water runs clear, then add it to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat </p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked </p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the <strong>mayo</strong> with the<strong> </strong>juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> – this is your <strong>lime mayo</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p><p>Crumble the <strong>feta</strong></p><p>Set everything aside for serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2192.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> to the plate and turn them several times until fully coated in all the spices – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
